---
import ApplicationLayout from '../layouts/ApplicationLayout.astro';

const title = "Industrial Centrifuge Sample Testing Case Studies";
const seoTitle = "Industrial Centrifuge Sample Testing Case Studies | Dolphin Centrifuge";
const description = "See anonymized industrial centrifuge sample testing examples from Dolphin Centrifuge, including wastewater, coolant, hydraulic oil, chemical slurry, glycol, and tramp oil separation results.";
const canonicalUrl = "https://dolphincentrifuge.com/sample-testing-case-studies/";

const articleJsonLd = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Article",
  "headline": seoTitle,
  "description": description,
  "author": {
    "@type": "Person",
    "name": "Sanjay Prabhu MSME",
    "jobTitle": "Centrifuge Applications Engineer",
    "worksFor": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "Dolphin Centrifuge" }
  },
  "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "Dolphin Centrifuge", "url": "https://dolphincentrifuge.com" },
  "url": canonicalUrl,
  "mainEntityOfPage": canonicalUrl,
  "datePublished": "2026-05-05",
  "dateModified": "2026-05-05"
};

const toc = [
  { id: "why-sample-testing", label: "Why Sample Testing Matters" },
  { id: "case-study-examples", label: "Sample Testing Result Examples", subItems: [
    { id: "case-chemical-slurry", label: "Chemical Slurry with High Solids" },
    { id: "case-hydraulic-oil", label: "Hydraulic Oil, Water, and Emulsion" },
    { id: "case-coolant", label: "Coolant with Tramp Oil and Sludge" },
    { id: "case-wastewater-carbon", label: "Wastewater with Fine Carbon Particles" },
    { id: "case-wastewater-color", label: "Wastewater with Dissolved Color" },
    { id: "case-glycol", label: "Glycol with Trace Suspended Solids" },
  ]},
  { id: "what-photos-show", label: "What the Photos Show" },
  { id: "how-to-use", label: "How to Use These Examples" },
  { id: "cost-limitations", label: "Cost and Limitations" },
];

const relatedApplications = [
  { label: "Industrial Centrifuge Sample Testing", href: "/industrial-centrifuge-sample-testing/" },
  { label: "Wastewater Centrifuge", href: "/wastewater-centrifuge/" },
  { label: "Coolant Centrifuge", href: "/machine-coolant-centrifuge/" },
  { label: "Hydraulic Oil Centrifuge", href: "/hydraulic-oil-centrifuge/" },
];

const relatedProducts = [
  { label: "DMPX-014 3-Phase Disc Centrifuge", href: "/dmpx-014-self-cleaning-3-phase-disc-stack-centrifuge/" },
  { label: "Decanter Centrifuge", href: "/decanter-centrifuge/" },
  { label: "Disc Stack Centrifuge", href: "/disc-stack-centrifuge/" },
];
---

<ApplicationLayout
  title={title}
  pageTitle={seoTitle}
  disableTitleSuffix={true}
  description={description}
  canonicalUrl={canonicalUrl}
  heroImage="/images/industrial-centrifuge-sample-testing/sample-testing-hero-2000.webp"
  heroImageAlt="Industrial centrifuge sample testing lab setup at Dolphin Centrifuge"
  category="knowledge"
  categoryLabel="Case Studies"
  categoryHref="/knowledge-case-studies/"
  hideBottomCTA={true}
  toc={toc}
  relatedApplications={relatedApplications}
  relatedProducts={relatedProducts}
  jsonLd={[articleJsonLd]}
>

  <!-- Intro -->
  <p>Dolphin Centrifuge tests customer samples before recommending equipment. These anonymized examples show how pilot-scale centrifuge testing helps identify whether a disc-stack centrifuge, decanter centrifuge, or two-stage system is the right fit. The examples below are summarized from real sample tests while keeping customer details private.</p>

  <!-- Section 1: Why Sample Testing Matters -->
  <h2 id="why-sample-testing">Why Sample Testing Matters</h2>

  <p>Centrifuge separation depends on the actual fluid, not just the industry name. Solids percentage, particle size, viscosity, temperature, oil-water balance, emulsions, and pre-treatment all affect the result. A small sample test helps answer three practical questions: can the separation be done, what type of centrifuge is appropriate, and what limitations need to be handled before a production system is selected.</p>

  <!-- 3-column summary -->
  <div class="not-prose grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-6">
    <div class="bg-navy/5 border-l-4 border-gold rounded-r-lg p-4">
      <p class="font-bold text-navy text-sm mb-1">Confirms Feasibility</p>
      <p class="text-text-light text-sm">Confirms if centrifugation works for the specific fluid.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-navy/5 border-l-4 border-gold rounded-r-lg p-4">
      <p class="font-bold text-navy text-sm mb-1">Shows Visual Result</p>
      <p class="text-text-light text-sm">Shows what separates visually before any equipment purchase.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-navy/5 border-l-4 border-gold rounded-r-lg p-4">
      <p class="font-bold text-navy text-sm mb-1">Guides Selection</p>
      <p class="text-text-light text-sm">Guides equipment selection based on observed separation behavior.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="not-prose my-6">
    <figure>
      <img
        src="/images/industrial-centrifuge-sample-testing/industrial-centrifuge-sample-testing-1024x371.webp"
        alt="Industrial centrifuge sample testing process overview at Dolphin Centrifuge"
        width="1024"
        height="371"
        loading="lazy"
        class="img-cap-800"
      />
      <figcaption><strong>Industrial centrifuge sample testing evaluates fluid behavior before equipment selection.</strong></figcaption>
    </figure>
  </div>

  <!-- Section 2: Case Study Examples -->
  <h2 id="case-study-examples">Sample Testing Result Examples</h2>

  <p>Each example below is drawn from a real sample test. Customer names and proprietary fluid details are not published. Results apply to the specific sample tested and are not a guarantee for different fluids.</p>

  <!-- Case 1: Chemical Slurry -->
  <div class="not-prose bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl shadow-sm overflow-hidden my-8">
    <div class="bg-navy px-6 py-4 flex items-center gap-3">
      <span class="bg-gold text-navy text-[11px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider px-2.5 py-1 rounded">Chemical Slurry</span>
      <h3 id="case-chemical-slurry" class="text-white font-bold text-lg leading-tight">Chemical Slurry with High Solids</h3>
    </div>
    <div class="p-6">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-5">
        <figure>
          <img
            src="/images/sample-testing-case-studies/chemical-slurry-before-after.webp"
            alt="Chemical slurry before and after centrifuge testing"
            width="702"
            height="876"
            loading="lazy"
            class="img-cap-400 rounded-lg"
          />
          <figcaption>Chemical slurry before and after centrifuge testing.</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure>
          <img
            src="/images/sample-testing-case-studies/chemical-slurry-separated-solids.webp"
            alt="Separated solids collected in the centrifuge bowl after chemical slurry testing"
            width="800"
            height="600"
            loading="lazy"
            class="img-cap-400 rounded-lg"
          />
          <figcaption>Separated solids collected in the centrifuge bowl after testing.</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
      <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden mb-4">
        <tbody class="bg-white">
          <tr class="border-t border-gray-100">
            <td class="px-4 py-2 font-medium text-navy w-36">Goal</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2 text-text-light">Remove fine suspended solids from a dense process liquid.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-t border-gray-100">
            <td class="px-4 py-2 font-medium text-navy">Test finding</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2 text-text-light">The pilot disc-stack test clarified the liquid and removed visible solids from the post-test sample.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-t border-gray-100">
            <td class="px-4 py-2 font-medium text-navy">Limitation</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2 text-text-light">The incoming sample had about 20% solids by volume, which is too high for a disc-stack centrifuge alone in production.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-t border-gray-100">
            <td class="px-4 py-2 font-medium text-navy">Recommendation</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2 text-text-light">Use a decanter centrifuge first to remove bulk solids, then use a self-cleaning disc-stack centrifuge for final polishing.</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-light border-l-4 border-gold/60 pl-4 italic">Takeaway: Testing showed the separation was possible, but also prevented the wrong single-machine recommendation.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Case 2: Hydraulic Oil -->
  <div class="not-prose bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl shadow-sm overflow-hidden my-8">
    <div class="bg-navy px-6 py-4 flex items-center gap-3">
      <span class="bg-gold text-navy text-[11px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider px-2.5 py-1 rounded">Oil-Water Separation</span>
      <h3 id="case-hydraulic-oil" class="text-white font-bold text-lg leading-tight">Hydraulic Oil, Water, Emulsion, and Solids</h3>
    </div>
    <div class="p-6">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-5">
        <figure>
          <img
            src="/images/sample-testing-case-studies/hydraulic-oil-water-three-phase-test.webp"
            alt="Hydraulic oil, water, and emulsion sample after 3-phase separation testing"
            width="1350"
            height="1800"
            loading="lazy"
            class="img-cap-400 rounded-lg"
          />
          <figcaption>Hydraulic oil, water, and emulsion sample after 3-phase separation testing.</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure>
          <img
            src="/images/sample-testing-case-studies/hydraulic-oil-bowl-solids.webp"
            alt="Fine solids collected during hydraulic oil separation testing"
            width="800"
            height="859"
            loading="lazy"
            class="img-cap-400 rounded-lg"
          />
          <figcaption>Fine solids collected during hydraulic oil separation testing.</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
      <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden mb-4">
        <tbody class="bg-white">
          <tr class="border-t border-gray-100">
            <td class="px-4 py-2 font-medium text-navy w-36">Goal</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2 text-text-light">Separate water from hydraulic oil and emulsion while removing fine solids.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-t border-gray-100">
            <td class="px-4 py-2 font-medium text-navy">Test finding</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2 text-text-light">Heating and pre-straining improved the separation. The heavy phase appeared as clean water, while oil and emulsion discharged as the light phase.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-t border-gray-100">
            <td class="px-4 py-2 font-medium text-navy">Recommendation</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2 text-text-light">Use a 3-phase self-cleaning disc-stack centrifuge, with pre-straining when large debris is present.</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-light border-l-4 border-gold/60 pl-4 italic">Takeaway: The test showed both the separation result and the needed pre-treatment step.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Case 3: Coolant -->
  <div class="not-prose bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl shadow-sm overflow-hidden my-8">
    <div class="bg-navy px-6 py-4 flex items-center gap-3">
      <span class="bg-gold text-navy text-[11px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider px-2.5 py-1 rounded">Coolant and Tramp Oil</span>
      <h3 id="case-coolant" class="text-white font-bold text-lg leading-tight">Coolant with Tramp Oil and Sludge</h3>
    </div>
    <div class="p-6">
      <div class="mb-5">
        <figure>
          <img
            src="/images/sample-testing-case-studies/coolant-tramp-oil-before-after.webp"
            alt="Coolant sample separated into clarified coolant and tramp oil"
            width="864"
            height="802"
            loading="lazy"
            class="img-cap-600 rounded-lg"
          />
          <figcaption>Coolant sample separated into clarified coolant and tramp oil.</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>

      <!-- Video: Coolant Tramp Oil Separation -->
      <div class="mb-5">
        <figure>
          <video
            controls
            preload="metadata"
            poster="/images/sample-testing-case-studies/coolant-tramp-oil-video-poster.webp"
            class="w-full rounded-lg shadow-md"
            style="max-width: 720px;"
          >
            <source src="/videos/sample-testing-case-studies/coolant-tramp-oil-sample-test.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
            Your browser does not support the video tag.
          </video>
          <figcaption>Pilot-scale centrifuge test showing coolant, tramp oil, and sludge separation behavior during sample testing.</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <p class="text-xs text-text-light bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-3 mt-3 leading-relaxed">
          <strong>Note:</strong> This video is for visual guidance only. Sample testing does not guarantee production-scale performance, final product quality, lab results, disposal approval, regulatory compliance, or commercial suitability.
        </p>
      </div>

      <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden mb-4">
        <tbody class="bg-white">
          <tr class="border-t border-gray-100">
            <td class="px-4 py-2 font-medium text-navy w-36">Goal</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2 text-text-light">Separate tramp oil and sludge from water-based manufacturing coolant.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-t border-gray-100">
            <td class="px-4 py-2 font-medium text-navy">Test finding</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2 text-text-light">The sample separated into clarified coolant, separated tramp oil, and collected sludge.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-t border-gray-100">
            <td class="px-4 py-2 font-medium text-navy">Recommendation</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2 text-text-light">Use a 3-phase self-cleaning disc-stack centrifuge in a kidney-loop setup on the coolant tank.</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-light border-l-4 border-gold/60 pl-4 italic">Takeaway: Sample testing can show whether coolant recovery is practical before investing in a full system.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Case 4: Wastewater Carbon Particles -->
  <div class="not-prose bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl shadow-sm overflow-hidden my-8">
    <div class="bg-navy px-6 py-4 flex items-center gap-3">
      <span class="bg-gold text-navy text-[11px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider px-2.5 py-1 rounded">Wastewater</span>
      <h3 id="case-wastewater-carbon" class="text-white font-bold text-lg leading-tight">Wastewater with Fine Carbon Particles</h3>
    </div>
    <div class="p-6">
      <div class="mb-5">
        <figure>
          <img
            src="/images/sample-testing-case-studies/wastewater-carbon-particles-before-after.webp"
            alt="Wastewater sample before and after fine suspended-solids removal by centrifuge"
            width="576"
            height="745"
            loading="lazy"
            class="img-cap-400 rounded-lg"
          />
          <figcaption>Wastewater sample before and after fine suspended-solids removal.</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
      <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden mb-4">
        <tbody class="bg-white">
          <tr class="border-t border-gray-100">
            <td class="px-4 py-2 font-medium text-navy w-36">Goal</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2 text-text-light">Remove fine suspended solids from industrial wastewater.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-t border-gray-100">
            <td class="px-4 py-2 font-medium text-navy">Test finding</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2 text-text-light">The disc-stack centrifuge removed nearly all visible suspended solids from the test sample.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-t border-gray-100">
            <td class="px-4 py-2 font-medium text-navy">Recommendation</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2 text-text-light">Use a self-cleaning disc-stack clarifier sized to the required plant flow rate.</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-light border-l-4 border-gold/60 pl-4 italic">Takeaway: The test confirmed that fine particle clarification was a good centrifuge application.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Case 5: Wastewater with Color -->
  <div class="not-prose bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl shadow-sm overflow-hidden my-8">
    <div class="bg-navy px-6 py-4 flex items-center gap-3">
      <span class="bg-gold text-navy text-[11px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider px-2.5 py-1 rounded">Wastewater Pre-Treatment</span>
      <h3 id="case-wastewater-color" class="text-white font-bold text-lg leading-tight">Wastewater with Dissolved Color and Cloudiness</h3>
    </div>
    <div class="p-6">
      <div class="mb-5">
        <figure>
          <img
            src="/images/sample-testing-case-studies/wastewater-charcoal-pretreatment-before-after.webp"
            alt="Wastewater sample tested with activated charcoal pre-treatment and centrifuge separation"
            width="659"
            height="949"
            loading="lazy"
            class="img-cap-400 rounded-lg"
          />
          <figcaption>Wastewater sample tested with activated charcoal pre-treatment and centrifuge separation.</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
      <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden mb-4">
        <tbody class="bg-white">
          <tr class="border-t border-gray-100">
            <td class="px-4 py-2 font-medium text-navy w-36">Goal</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2 text-text-light">Improve wastewater clarity beyond basic suspended-solids removal.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-t border-gray-100">
            <td class="px-4 py-2 font-medium text-navy">Test finding</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2 text-text-light">Centrifugation removed suspended solids. Activated charcoal pre-treatment improved visual clarity by adsorbing material that centrifugation alone could not remove.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-t border-gray-100">
            <td class="px-4 py-2 font-medium text-navy">Recommendation</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2 text-text-light">Pair chemical or adsorbent pre-treatment with centrifuge separation when dissolved or colloidal contaminants are present.</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-light border-l-4 border-gold/60 pl-4 italic">Takeaway: A centrifuge removes separable solids. Testing helps reveal when pre-treatment is needed.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Case 6: Glycol -->
  <div class="not-prose bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl shadow-sm overflow-hidden my-8">
    <div class="bg-navy px-6 py-4 flex items-center gap-3">
      <span class="bg-gold text-navy text-[11px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider px-2.5 py-1 rounded">Glycol and Antifreeze</span>
      <h3 id="case-glycol" class="text-white font-bold text-lg leading-tight">Glycol and Water with Trace Suspended Solids</h3>
    </div>
    <div class="p-6">
      <div class="mb-5">
        <figure>
          <img
            src="/images/sample-testing-case-studies/glycol-trace-solids-before-after.webp"
            alt="Glycol and water sample with trace suspended solids before and after centrifuge testing"
            width="1792"
            height="2400"
            loading="lazy"
            class="img-cap-400 rounded-lg"
          />
          <figcaption>Glycol and water sample with trace suspended solids before and after testing.</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
      <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden mb-4">
        <tbody class="bg-white">
          <tr class="border-t border-gray-100">
            <td class="px-4 py-2 font-medium text-navy w-36">Goal</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2 text-text-light">Determine whether centrifugation could visibly clarify a low-solids glycol sample.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-t border-gray-100">
            <td class="px-4 py-2 font-medium text-navy">Test finding</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2 text-text-light">The sample contained only trace solids, and the before and after samples looked nearly identical by eye.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-t border-gray-100">
            <td class="px-4 py-2 font-medium text-navy">Recommendation</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2 text-text-light">Return samples for lab analysis before recommending equipment.</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-light border-l-4 border-gold/60 pl-4 italic">Takeaway: A good test is not always a sales pitch. Sometimes it shows that a centrifuge may not be worth buying for that fluid.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Section 3: What the Photos Show -->
  <h2 id="what-photos-show">What the Photos Show</h2>

  <p>Before and after photos are useful, but they are not the whole test. Dolphin also checks bowl contents, separated phases, temperature sensitivity, solids loading, and whether a pre-filter, heat, chemical aid, decanter, or disc-stack centrifuge is the right next step.</p>

  <div class="not-prose grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-6">
    <figure>
      <img
        src="/images/sample-testing-case-studies/chemical-slurry-separated-solids.webp"
        alt="Bowl contents showing separated solids from chemical slurry centrifuge test"
        width="800"
        height="600"
        loading="lazy"
        class="img-cap-400 rounded-lg"
      />
      <figcaption>Chemical slurry bowl solids after testing.</figcaption>
    </figure>
    <figure>
      <img
        src="/images/sample-testing-case-studies/hydraulic-oil-bowl-solids.webp"
        alt="Bowl solids from hydraulic oil and water centrifuge separation test"
        width="800"
        height="859"
        loading="lazy"
        class="img-cap-400 rounded-lg"
      />
      <figcaption>Hydraulic oil test bowl solids.</figcaption>
    </figure>
    <figure>
      <img
        src="/images/industrial-centrifuge-sample-testing/algae-samples-before-after-test-tubes-400.webp"
        alt="Before and after test tube samples from industrial centrifuge testing"
        width="400"
        height="533"
        loading="lazy"
        class="img-cap-400 rounded-lg"
      />
      <figcaption>Before and after test tube samples from industrial centrifuge testing.</figcaption>
    </figure>
  </div>

  <!-- Section 4: How to Use These Examples -->
  <h2 id="how-to-use">How to Use These Examples</h2>

  <p>These examples are not guarantees for a different fluid. They are proof of the testing method. If your sample has similar contamination, Dolphin can test your actual material and provide a practical recommendation based on observed separation results.</p>

  <!-- Section 5: Cost and Limitations -->
  <h2 id="cost-limitations">Sample Testing Cost and Limitations</h2>

  <p>Sample testing is a chargeable service. The cost depends on the type of sample, whether heating is required, whether the test is 2-phase clarification or 3-phase separation, the setup and cleaning time required, and whether separated sample phases need to be returned. Return shipping and special handling are quoted separately when applicable.</p>

  <p>The test results are for guidance only. They do not guarantee production-scale performance, final product quality, regulatory compliance, disposal approval, customer lab results, or commercial suitability. Full-scale results can vary based on flow rate, temperature, feed consistency, solids loading, chemistry, upstream treatment, and equipment configuration.</p>

  <!-- Bottom CTA -->
  <div class="not-prose bg-navy/5 border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 md:p-8 mt-8">
    <h3 class="text-navy font-bold text-xl mb-2">Want to test your own sample?</h3>
    <p class="text-text-light text-sm mb-5">Send Dolphin Centrifuge a representative sample and we will evaluate separation performance, document the visual results, and recommend the appropriate centrifuge path.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-3">
      <a href="/industrial-centrifuge-sample-testing/" class="inline-block bg-gold text-navy font-bold px-6 py-2.5 rounded-lg hover:bg-yellow-500 transition-colors text-sm">Request Sample Testing</a>
      <a href="/contact-for-alfa-laval-centrifuges/" class="inline-block border border-navy text-navy font-semibold px-6 py-2.5 rounded-lg hover:bg-navy/5 transition-colors text-sm">Contact Dolphin</a>
    </div>
  </div>

</ApplicationLayout>
